FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FThe service will be attended by The
OL,7,FPrince and Princess of Wales, the
OL,8,FPrime Minister Sir Keir Starmer and
OL,9,FOpposition Leader Kemi Badenoch. Other
OL,10,Fsenior members of the Royal Family,
OL,11,FAnglican clergy and diverse guests
OL,12,Fincluding faith leaders, charities,
OL,13,Fhealthcare workers and school children
OL,14,Fwill also be attendance.
OL,16,FAs well as family and friends, the
OL,17,FArchbishop - who was a nurse before
OL,18,Fbecoming ordained - has also invited
OL,19,FNHS nurses and carers working in
OL,20,Fhospitals and hospices in Canterbury.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FIt comes as she told ITV Meridian on
OL,7,FThursday (19 March) that her
OL,8,Fenthronement should still go ahead as
OL,9,Fplanned despite the outbreak of
OL,10,Fmeningitis in the city, with two
OL,11,Fstudents dead and 29 cases confirmed.
OL,13,FThe service will include a Mandate
OL,14,Ffrom His Majesty The King giving
OL,15,Finstruction to install Archbishop
OL,16,FSarah, and see her deliver her
OL,17,Finaugural sermon as Archbishop of
OL,18,FCanterbury.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FFive of the 'Africa Six' - the first
OL,7,Ffemale Anglican bishops from across
OL,8,FAfrica - will be among some who will
OL,9,Fprocess through the Cathedral's nave.
OL,11,FThere will be a Kyrie sung in Urdu and
OL,12,Freadings, prayers, music and a
OL,13,Fblessing in six languages including
OL,14,FEnglish. The music to greet the
OL,15,Fproclamation of the Gospel will be
OL,16,Fprovided by the African Choir of
OL,17,FNorfolk with their members drawn from
OL,18,Fa wide range of countries.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FThe service will blend choral music
OL,7,Fled by the Cathedral Choir with music
OL,8,Ffrom around the Communion, featuring a
OL,9,FKyrie sung in Urdu and readings,
OL,10,Fprayers, music and a blessing, in six
OL,11,Flanguages including English.
OL,13,FThe music to greet the proclamation of
OL,14,Fthe Gospel will be provided by the
OL,15,FAfrican Choir of Norfolk with their
OL,16,Fmembers drawn from a wide range of
OL,17,Fcountries. There will also be a
OL,18,Fcelebration of the contribution to the
OL,19,FChurch by female scholars, musicians
OL,20,Fand writers.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FIn other firsts, the Corporal Oath,
OL,7,Fwhen Archbishop Sarah will lay her
OL,8,Fhand on the Bible and swear to respect
OL,9,Fthe historical rights of the
OL,10,FCathedral, will be sworn for the first
OL,11,Ftime on the St John's Bible.
OL,13,FThe cope and mitre worn by Archbishop
OL,14,FSarah were commissioned when she was
OL,15,Ffirst consecrated, with the clasp made
OL,16,Ffrom the belt buckle she wore as a
OL,17,Fnurse while serving in the NHS.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FAt the end of the service, Archbishop
OL,7,FSarah will greet the Prince and
OL,8,FPrincess of Wales outside the West
OL,9,FDoor of the Cathedral. From there she
OL,10,Fwill walk through the Christ Church
OL,11,FGate of the cathedral precinct and
OL,12,Fpray a blessing on the city and the
OL,13,Fdiocese.
OL,15,FThe Archbishop of Canterbury, The Most
OL,16,FRevd Sarah Mullally, said: "As I
OL,17,Fprepare to begin my ministry as
OL,18,FArchbishop of Canterbury, I am
OL,19,Fgrateful for the prayers and support I
OL,20,Fhave received from people here and
OL,21,Faround the world.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,F"To be welcomed into the city and
OL,7,Fdiocese of Canterbury is an immense
OL,8,Fprivilege ` and I am grateful to be
OL,9,Fsharing in this moment with people of
OL,10,Fall ages and backgrounds from across
OL,11,Fthe Church of England, the Anglican
OL,12,FCommunion, our nation and the world.
OL,14,F"Our world today needs the love,
OL,15,Fhealing and hope that we find in Jesus
OL,16,FChrist. I continue to pray that we
OL,17,Frenew our confidence in this good
OL,18,Fnews, and recommit ourselves to
OL,19,Fsharing the joy of the Gospel."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1774094594
OL,3,CFirst female Archbishop of Canterbury
OL,4,Cinstallation to host 2,000 guests
OL,6,FDean of Canterbury, The Very Reverend
OL,7,FDr David Monteith, said "each new
OL,8,FArchbishop brings their own particular
OL,9,Fgifts and experiences to the role with
OL,10,Fa sense of renewed hope."
OL,12,F"Installing Sarah as our first female
OL,13,FArchbishop would have almost been
OL,14,Funimaginable even 50 years ago," he
OL,15,Fsaid. "Today matters. As we combine
OL,16,Fcenturies of tradition in this ancient
OL,17,Fservice with those elements unique to
OL,18,FSarah's ministry, we welcome her to
OL,19,Four Cathedral and diocese, and pray
OL,20,Ffor her as she takes on the role of
OL,21,FArchbishop of Canterbury."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G9/10
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
